	"info": {
		"_postman_id": "b2c3d4e5-f6a7-8901-bcde-f12345678901",
		"name": "IRoad Mobile Driver APIs",
		"description": "## IRoad Mobile Driver APIs\n\n### Base URL\nUse environment variable `{{base_url}}` (no trailing slash). Full paths begin with `/api/v1/mobile/`.\n\nExample: `http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/mobile/driver/auth/login/`\n\n### Standard JSON envelope\n```json\n{\n  \"status\": 1,\n  \"message\": \"…\",\n  \"data\": { }\n}\n```\n- **status `1`**: Success (`data` may be empty `{}`).\n- **status `0`**: Validation or business error; `data` often includes `errors` (DRF serializer shape) or extra fields such as `attempts_remaining`.\n- **status `2`**: Authentication failure (e.g. missing/invalid/expired JWT) — HTTP **401**; used by the mobile API exception handler for auth failures.\n\n### Headers\n| Header | When |\n|--------|------|\n| **X-Tenant-ID** | Send tenant profile UUID or schema name when tenant middleware cannot resolve the host; required for correct tenant DB in many deployments. |\n| **X-Language** | Optional: `en` or `ar` for translated `message` strings. |\n| **Authorization** | `Bearer {{access_token}}` on all **authenticated** routes. |\n| **Content-Type** | `application/json` for JSON bodies. For profile photo, use **multipart/form-data** (field `profile_photo`); Postman sets the boundary automatically. |\n\n### Login and tokens\n1. Set `base_url`, `email`, `password`, and `tenant_id` (if needed) in the **IRoad Mobile Driver — Local** environment.\n2. Run **Login**. The **Tests** script saves `access_token` and `refresh_token` into the active environment.\n3. Call protected endpoints with **Bearer** `access_token`.\n\n> Refresh-token exchange is not part of this collection unless you add it separately; tokens are issued by the mobile auth service.\n\n### Forgot password / reset (unauthenticated)\n1. **Forgot Password** — `POST` with `email`.\n2. **Verify OTP** — `POST` with `email` and `otp_code` from email/SMS.\n3. **Reset Password** — `POST` with `email`, `otp_code`, `new_password`, `confirm_password`.\n\n### Change password while logged in (OTP)\n1. **Request OTP** — `POST` with `send_via`: `email` or `mobile` (SMS requires a phone number on the driver profile).\n2. **Verify Change Password OTP** — `POST` with `otp_code`.\n3. **Change Password** — `POST` with `current_password`, `new_password`, `confirm_password`, `otp_code`.\n\n### Profile\n- **Get Profile** — `GET` returns driver/profile payload in `data`.\n- **Update Profile Photo** — `POST` or `PATCH` same URL; **form-data** key **`profile_photo`** (image file: jpg, jpeg, png, webp; max 10 MB).\n\n### Logout\n`POST` with **Bearer** access token; empty body. Invalidates the current access token server-side where implemented.",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
	},
	"item": [
		{
			"name": "Driver Auth",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "Login",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"try {",
									"    var json = pm.response.json();",
									"    if (json && json.status === 1 && json.data) {",
									"        if (json.data.access_token) {",
									"            pm.environment.set(\"access_token\", json.data.access_token);",
									"        }",
									"        if (json.data.refresh_token) {",
									"            pm.environment.set(\"refresh_token\", json.data.refresh_token);",
									"        }",
									"    }",
									"} catch (e) {",
									"    console.warn(\"Could not parse login JSON or save tokens:\", e);",
									"}"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript"
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json"
							},
							{
								"key": "X-Tenant-ID",
								"value": "{{tenant_id}}",
								"description": "Tenant UUID or schema name when needed"
							},
							{
								"key": "X-Language",
								"value": "en",
								"description": "Optional: en | ar"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{email}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{password}}\"\n}",
							"options": {
								"raw": {
									"language": "json"
								}
							}
						},
						"url": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/mobile/driver/auth/login/",
						"description": "Authenticate driver. On success, `data` contains `access_token`, `refresh_token`, and `driver`."
					},
					"response": [
						{
							"name": "Login success",
							"originalRequest": {
								"method": "POST",
								"header": [],
								"body": {
									"mode": "raw",
									"raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"driver@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"Password@123\"\n}"
								},
								"url": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/mobile/driver/auth/login/"
							},
							"status": "OK",
							"code": 200,
							"_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
							"header": [],
							"body": "{\n  \"status\": 1,\n  \"message\": \"Login successful.\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"access_token\": \"eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...\",\n    \"refresh_token\": \"eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...\",\n    \"driver\": {\n      \"driver_id\": \"uuid\",\n      \"driver_code\": \"DRV001\",\n      \"english_name\": \"John Driver\",\n      \"arabic_name\": null,\n      \"driver_status\": \"active\"\n    }\n  }\n}"
						},
						{
							"name": "Invalid credentials",
							"originalRequest": {
								"method": "POST",
								"header": [],
								"body": {
									"mode": "raw",
									"raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"driver@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"WrongPassword\"\n}"
								},
								"url": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/mobile/driver/auth/login/"
							},
							"status": "Unauthorized",
							"code": 401,
							"_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
							"header": [],
							"body": "{\n  \"status\": 0,\n  \"message\": \"Invalid email or password.\",\n  \"data\": {}\n}"
						}
					]
				},
				{
